<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-07T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-07T13:00:00-05:00" n="147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3419/1448: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-07T14:00:00-04:00">July 7, 1938—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>88. For Braden from the Under Secretary. Your 184, July 6, 10 a.m. This
                            development is most encouraging. The procedure outlined in paragraph
                                (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) has the approval of the President. Please
                                <pb facs="0171" n="162" xml:id="pg_162"/> telegraph immediately what
                            statement the Department may give to the press here and the time at
                            which such statement may be released.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>